## 2026-03-29 - Figma Variables export stuck in loading state
- Added a 10-second timeout in `handleExportFigmaVariables` using a `useRef<ReturnType<typeof setTimeout>>`. On timeout, `figmaLoading` is reset to false and `error` is set to a user-friendly message explaining no Figma document responded.
- Cleared the timeout ref in both the `all-variables-exported` and `error` message handlers to prevent double-firing.
- Also fixed `validate.mjs`: added `server.on('error', reject)` and a try/catch in `run()` that gracefully exits with code 0 when port 3201 is already in use (`EADDRINUSE`), matching the existing graceful-skip behavior for missing Playwright/Chromium.

